        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 2:46PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 245 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Greenville, moving west at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Greenville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
